quran[7{c,v,t}:
2,135,"aur ( yahodi aur isaai ) kehte hain ke yahodi ya isaai ho jao to seedhay raste par lag jao. ( ae paighambar un se ) keh do, ( nahi ) balkay ( hum ) deen ibrahim ( ikhtiyar kiye hue hain ) jo aik khuda ke ho rahay they aur mushrikon mein se nah they"
2,136,"( mslmano ) kaho ke hum khuda par imaan laaye aur jo ( kitaab ) hum par utri, is par aur jo ( saheefay ) ibrahim aur asmayl aur Ishaq aur Yaqoob aur un ki aulaad par nazil hue un par aur jo ( kitaaben ) moose aur eesa ko ataa huien, un par, aur jo aur payghambaroon ko un ke perwar-digaar ki taraf se milein, un par ( sab par imaan laaye ) hum un peghambaron mein se kisi mein kuch farq nahi karte aur hum isi ( khuday-e wahid ) ke farmanbardar hain"
2,137,to agar yeh log bhi isi terhan imaan le ayen jis terhan tum imaan le aeye ho to hadaayat yab ho jayen aur agar munh phair len ( aur nah manen ) to woh ( tumhare ) mukhalif hain aur un ke muqablay mein tumhen khuda kaafi hai. aur woh suneney wala ( aur ) jan-nay wala hai
2,138,( keh do ke hum ne ) khuda ka rang ( ikhtiyar kar liya hai ) aur khuda se behtar rang kis ka ho sakta hai. aur hum isi ki ibadat karne walay hain
2,139,"( un se ) kaho,kiya tum khuda ke baray mein hum se jhagarte ho, halaank wohi hamara aur tumahra perwar-digaar hai aur hum ko hamaray aamaal ( ka badla miley ga ) aur tum ko tumhare aamaal ( ka ) aur hum khaas isi ki ibadat karne walay hain"
2,140,"( ae yahood wa nasari )kiya tum is baat ke qaail ho ke ibrahim aur asmayl aur Ishaq aur Yaqoob aur un ki aulaad yahodi ya isaai they. ( ae Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihiwasallam un se ) kaho ke bhala tum ziyada jantay ho ya khuda? aur is se barh kar zalim kon, jo khuda ki shahadat ko, jo is ke paas ( kitaab mein mojood ) hai chupaye. aur jo kuch tum kar rahay ho, khuda is se ghaafil nahi"
2,141,"yeh jamaat guzar chuki. un ko woh ( miley ga ) jo unhon nekiya, aur tum ko woh jo tum nekiya. aur jo amal woh karte they, is ki prssh tum se nahi hogi"
